# MktMoves Web — Cline Rules

## Memory Bank — Read First, Always

At the start of EVERY task, before writing any code or making any plan,
read these files in order:

1. memory-bank/projectBrief.md
2. memory-bank/techContext.md
3. memory-bank/designSystem.md
4. memory-bank/codebaseStructure.md
5. memory-bank/activeContext.md

Do not skip any of these. Do not proceed until all five are read.

## Critical Constraints

- Do NOT use the terminal to read or scan any files.
- Do NOT open or read `references/homepage.html`. All design decisions
  from that file have been extracted into memory-bank/designSystem.md.
  That file is the authoritative design reference.
- Do NOT install any new npm packages without explicit instruction.
- Do NOT use Tailwind classes. Plain CSS only, using CSS variables.
- Do NOT use any UI component library (no Radix, no shadcn, no Headless UI).
- Do NOT modify these files: app/api/waitlist/route.ts, lib/supabase.ts,
  .env.local, .env.example, next.config.ts, tsconfig.json.

## Scope Discipline

- Only build what the current prompt asks for. Do not add features,
  pages, or components that were not requested.
- If a task is ambiguous, state the ambiguity and ask before writing code.
- After completing a task, update memory-bank/activeContext.md with what
  was built and what the next task is.

## Code Standards

- TypeScript strict mode. No `any` types.
- All colors via CSS variables. No hardcoded hex values in components.
- All spacing via CSS variables or multiples of 4px.
- IBM Plex Mono for all numerical data only. IBM Plex Sans for everything else.
- Server components by default. Add "use client" only when required
  (search inputs, interactive state).
